                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d182">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1635</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MCK1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moser</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-26T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 20, <hi rend="italic">2</hi> p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d182fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_127">p. 127</ref>.</note> last
                    sentence. Department has no objection to your obtaining evidence regarding
                    occurrences at Blagoveshchensk provided you can do so unofficially and without
                    implying any recognition of Far Eastern Committee or affording any indication
                        <pb facs="0229" n="139" xml:id="pg_139"/> of prejudice on the part of this
                    Government against any particular elements in Russia. Department can not
                    authorize appointment of a delegate to sit with committee.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
